---
/**
 * Avondale Personal Injury Attorneys — Location Page
 * West Valley. I-10 corridor. 99th & Lower Buckeye: #4 most dangerous intersection.
 */

import PracticeAreaLayout from '../layouts/PracticeAreaLayout.astro';
import { getLocalBusinessSchema } from '../utils/schema';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How long do I have to file an injury claim in Avondale?',
    answer: 'Two years from the date of the crash under ARS 12-542. For wrongful death, two years from the date of death. Evidence disappears fast in this corridor. Surveillance footage from businesses near crash sites gets overwritten on 30-day loops.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What are the most dangerous roads in Avondale?',
    answer: 'Avondale Boulevard and McDowell Road, Dysart Road and Indian School Road, and the industrial corridors near 107th Avenue are known crash zones. 99th Avenue and Lower Buckeye Road ranked 4th on MAG\'s Top 100 most dangerous intersections with 411 crashes over the study period.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you have an office in Avondale?',
    answer: 'Our offices are in Buckeye and Maricopa. Avondale is between both locations. We handle cases across the West Valley and know Avondale\'s roads, school districts, and the industrial corridors where truck traffic concentrates.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What about school bus crashes in Avondale?',
    answer: 'We recovered $800,000 from Hartford Insurance for a special needs child left on a school bus. Avondale is served by the Littleton, Avondale, and Agua Fria school districts. If your child was injured on a school bus or school grounds, the 180-day notice of claim deadline for government entities is critical.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What does it cost to hire an injury attorney?',
    answer: 'Nothing upfront. Contingency basis. You pay nothing unless we recover money for you. The consultation is free.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I recover compensation if I was partially at fault?',
    answer: 'Yes. Arizona\'s pure comparative negligence rule under ARS 12-2505 reduces your recovery by your fault percentage but doesn\'t eliminate it.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What types of cases do you handle in Avondale?',
    answer: 'Car crashes, truck crashes, pedestrian injuries, school bus crashes, wrongful death, slip and fall, elder abuse, nursing home abuse, medical negligence, and dog bites. If someone else\'s negligence caused your injury in Avondale, we want to hear about it.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What about truck crashes near the industrial zones?',
    answer: 'The 107th Avenue corridor and the I-10 frontage roads near Avondale carry heavy commercial truck traffic from distribution centers and warehouses. We handle truck crash cases and pull FMCSA carrier records, ELD data, and maintenance logs on every case.',
  },
];

const localSchema = getLocalBusinessSchema('Avondale', 'avondale');
---

<PracticeAreaLayout
  title="Avondale Personal Injury Attorneys"
  description="Avondale injury attorneys at AZ Law Now. 99th Ave and Lower Buckeye: 4th most dangerous intersection in the Valley. Free consultation. Call (602) 654-0202."
  canonical="/avondale/"
  practiceArea="Avondale Personal Injury Attorneys"
  heroTitle="99th and Lower Buckeye: 4th Most Dangerous Intersection in the Valley."
  heroSubtitle="Avondale injury attorneys who know the industrial corridors, the school districts, and the intersections where crashes concentrate."
  heroImage="/images/heroes/avondale.webp"
  faqs={faqs}
  schema={localSchema}
>
  <p>
    99th Avenue and Lower Buckeye Road. MAG ranked it the 4th most dangerous intersection in the entire Maricopa County metro area. 411 crashes over the study period. It's in Avondale. And it's the kind of intersection I pull ADOT data on every time a client calls from this area.
  </p>

  <p>
    Avondale sits right in the middle of the West Valley corridor between Phoenix and Buckeye. I-10 runs along its southern edge. Industrial zones near 107th Avenue generate truck traffic that mixes with residential commuter traffic. School districts overlap. Construction projects change lane configurations quarterly. The roads are complicated, and the crash data reflects it.
  </p>

  <h2>The Industrial Corridor Problem</h2>

  <p>
    The area around 107th Avenue and the I-10 frontage roads carries heavy commercial traffic. Distribution centers, warehouses, and logistics operations have expanded rapidly along this corridor. More trucks means more conflict points with passenger vehicles, especially at intersections where turning trucks block sight lines and left-turn movements become gambles.
  </p>

  <p>
    The <a href="/insights/truck-crashes-maricopa-county-data/">truck crash data for Maricopa County</a> shows 14,069 trucks involved in Arizona crashes in 2024. When a loaded semi hits a passenger car, 97% of fatalities are in the car. The weight difference is 23 to 1.
  </p>

  <h2>The $800,000 School Bus Case</h2>

  <p>
    We recovered $800,000 from Hartford Insurance for a special needs child who was left on a school bus. That case came from this corridor. Avondale is served by the Littleton Elementary School District, the Avondale Elementary School District, and the Agua Fria Union High School District.
  </p>

  <p>
    If your child was injured on a school bus or at school, the clock is different. Claims against government entities in Arizona require a notice of claim within 180 days under ARS 12-821.01. Miss that deadline and the court won't hear your case, regardless of how strong it is. The <a href="/insights/arizona-school-bus-seat-belts/">school bus safety investigation</a> and the <a href="/insights/arizona-school-restraint-data/">school restraint data</a> I published cover the broader patterns.
  </p>

  <h2>Where Avondale Crashes Concentrate</h2>

  <p>
    Beyond the 99th and Lower Buckeye intersection, Avondale Boulevard and McDowell Road is a persistent crash zone. Dysart Road and Indian School Road handles cross-Valley commuter traffic at speeds the intersection geometry wasn't designed for. The I-10 Dysart Road interchange concentrates freeway-speed merges into a tight area.
  </p>

  <p>
    The <a href="/insights/west-valley-dangerous-intersections/">West Valley dangerous intersections investigation</a> covers the MAG data in detail. Avondale's intersections show up because the city sits at the crossroads of residential growth, industrial expansion, and freeway traffic.
  </p>

  <h2>Pedestrian Risk on Avondale Arterials</h2>

  <p>
    Arizona's pedestrian fatality rate is nearly twice the national average. The <a href="/insights/arizona-pedestrian-deaths-road-design/">pedestrian deaths investigation</a> shows that wide arterials, missing crosswalks, and insufficient lighting are the primary design factors. Avondale's arterials fit that profile. The MAG arterial widening project for Lower Buckeye Road focuses on "roadway capacity" but includes pedestrian improvements that have been needed for years.
  </p>

  <h2>Between Both Offices</h2>

  <p>
    Avondale sits between our Buckeye headquarters and our Maricopa office. We're accessible from either direction. When I investigate a crash at 99th and Lower Buckeye or along the I-10 frontage roads, I'm working roads I already know.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you or someone in your family was in a crash in Avondale, call <a href="tel:+16026540202">(602) 654-0202</a> or use our contact form. The consultation is free. We don't charge unless we recover money for you.
  </p>
</PracticeAreaLayout>
